misconceptions.correct_understanding:
Q4 specifically tests your ability to use loops to generate a text pattern. A minimal correct structure would look like:

```java
Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);
System.out.print("Enter height: ");
int n = input.nextInt();

for (int row = 1; row <= n; row++) {
    for (int col = 1; col <= row; col++) {
        System.out.print("*");
    }
    System.out.println(); // move to next line after each row
}
```

The program should not compute distances or areas; it should only use loops and printing to create the right triangle of stars.

